AGI - After the threats arrived from Iran after the killing in Damascus of two high commanders of the Force alQuds of the Iranian revolutionary Guards, Hassan Mahdavi, the spokesman of the Idf, the Israeli army, announced that "it was decided to strengthen and recruit reservists for the air defense system". The Israeli newspaper Yedioth Ahronoth.&nbsp;&nbsp reports it; Today Israel will also deliberately alter Gps services across the country to prevent possible attacks with missiles or drones.
&nbsp;
"Today the security system has begun to activate the Gps disorder throughout the country, including the center, as part of the preparations for Iranian revenge and the launch of cruise missiles, drones and missiles led to Israel," said Israeli public broadcaster Kan. For this reason, users of the localization application Waze, produced in Israel, will see the interference and will be recognized at all times as if they were in Beirut, Lebanon. The army also suspended all the congedes at home for combat troops.
&nbsp;
The security agency Shin Bet said it had invented the plans of a cell of Israeli Palestinians and Arabs who wanted to carry out attacks in Israel and the West Bank, as well as the national security minister Itamar Ben Gvir. Seven Israeli Arabs and four Palestinians from the West Bank were stopped. According to Shin Bet, the cell planned attacks against the Idf bases and other sensitive sites, including Ben Gurion airport and the government complex in Jerusalem. The Israeli press writes it.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
The Supreme Guide of Iran, the Ayatollah Ali Khamenei, said that Israel will be "slapped" in response to the attack on the Iranian consulate in Damascus, in which seven men of the Pasdaran were killed, two of whom were generals. "The defeat of the Zionist regime in Gaza will continue and this regime will be close to decline and dissolution," said Khamenei in a speech to Tehran. "Desperate people like what they have committed in Syria will not save them from defeat. Of course, they too will be slapped for that action." Khamenei warned Israel that he will repent. "With the help of God, we will make sure that the Zionists repent of their crime of aggression against the Iranian consulate in Damascus," said Khamenei in a morning post on X in Hebrew.

